Your ISBN-10 and my ISBN-13 both refer to the same book (I assume you got your ISBN from the copyright page, not from what some other dude said). Jan 1 2010 is the release date. The production date stamp of my e-copy is Dec 15 2010 and meetyourbrain.com headers and footers have been added to each and every page sometimes interfering with contents. (meetyourbrain.com provides homework help for this text; related to cramster.com) Your page count is for the print copy. The page count for the e-copy I have is 1381 = 1368 + 13 others (mostly reference/reminder pages). PDF size is 54.5 MB (after repair for Adobe and retooling of bookmarks).

If you can (losslessly) compress significantly below 25 MB, post. I said significantly. ;-)   Anyway, statistics show that people prefer by far uncompressed (and sometimes broken) files... They then simply cut on seeding not to bust their monthly BW cap. [sigh]
